---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../config';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use | RecastWise"
  description="Terms of use for RecastWise: free educational mortgage estimates, not financial advice, standard disclaimers."
  path="/terms/"
>
  <div class="wrap">
    <article class="prose" style="padding-block: 2rem;">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: July 3, 2026</em></p>

      <h2>What RecastWise is</h2>
      <p>
        RecastWise provides free, educational calculators and articles about mortgage recasting and related topics. By
        using the site you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Not financial, tax, or legal advice</h2>
      <p>
        Everything here is general information and estimation, not advice for your specific situation. Actual loan
        terms — recast fees, minimum lump sums, seasoning, eligibility, and payoff figures — are set by your servicer
        and investor and can differ from our estimates and the general ranges we cite. Always confirm the binding
        numbers with your servicer's written recast agreement, and consult a qualified professional before making
        financial decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>No warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The site is provided "as is." We work to keep the math correct and the lender data current, but we make no
        warranty that the site is error-free and accept no liability for decisions made based on it.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You may link to, share, and print RecastWise's output for personal use. You may not scrape, republish, or resell the site's content.</p>

      <h2>Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        RecastWise displays ads served by third parties (Google AdSense). Advertisers are responsible for their own
        content; an ad's presence is not our endorsement. See our <a href="/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a> for how
        advertising cookies work.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms; continued use after changes means you accept them.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
